column2: To comfortably organise your congresses, seminars and exhibitions, the CICG can accommodate up to 2'200 people in its spacious rooms with variable configuration and equipped with cutting-edge technology.

The Centre offers 19 conference rooms of 20 to 300 sitting places, 2 large rooms with 350 to 1'000 places (that can be organized to bring the capacity to 2'200 sitting places), 60 offices, 1 multipurpose space of 600sqm, 1 post office, 2 bars and 1 restaurant for 600 guests.
It benefits from a privileged location in close proximity to the Place des Nations, the main International Organisations and permanent missions based in Geneva.
We are situated ten minutes from the airport or the centre of town, and right in the middle of Geneva's International area. Reaching us has never been so easy.
Parking facilities are available 50 metres from our centres.
The International Conference Centre Geneva (CICG) can accommodate your events with up to 3000 people, and make it possible to respond appropriately to your most demanding needs.
The multifunctional infrastructure of the CICG provides valuable solutions and combinations, whatever your project.
We offer flexible solutions to bring your event to achievement, be it large or small. Our expertise will be focused toward the success of your event.
To comfortably accommodate your congresses, seminars and exhibitions, the CICG places at your disposal 22 rooms with 20 to 2'200 seats as well as multipurpose spaces, offices and restaurant areas.

column1: Discover the different areas of the International Conference Centre of Geneva on all levels. We have 5 level:
Discover the rooms on Level +3. In addition, you can discover the VIP room and access points to the balconies of amphitheater D.
Discover Level +2 with its rooms, double and individual offices, as well as its multi-purpose spaces.
On Level 1 you find Amphitheatre D, the largest room in the CICG. In addition, on this floor you also find the restaurant and its terrace.
The main entrance to the Centre is found on Level 0. It gives direct access to our main large rooms on this floor. The Multi-Purpose Space and the coffee le 6eme continent complete this level.
Discover the different small- and medium-capacity rooms throughout Level -1. For medical needs, the infirmary is also found on this level. The floor is completed by double and individual offices.
The four main rooms, equipped with interpretation booths for six to eight languages, can be used independently, or else put together to make a single large plenary room.

column2: Totally multipurpose spaces are situated on different floors of the CICG.
They can be arranged according to your needs and used as conference rooms, exhibition and poster areas or as press centres.
The keywords of the CICG are flexibility and modularity.

column2: At Level 0, the Leman Bar is there to satisfy all your wishes through light catering, proposing breakfast, sandwiches, salads and refreshments. LEspace Voyage invites you to discover a new menu everyday drawn from world cuisine.

Mixing garden vegetables, local products, meats and fishes, as well as a dessert buffet, this will let you compose a menu of choice. In the relaxed atmosphere of the central bar, you will find gourmet sandwiches made to order, as well as hot and cold soups of the day.

The comfortable armchairs and the generously-sized tables are greatly appreciated.
The various multi-purpose spaces, situated on several levels, can be rearranged according to your needs.
Many offices from 1 to 4 places, as well as a luxurious VIP room, complete our offer.

The best choices adapted to the rooms and spaces to guarantee your success.

Bus 5: Depart from Gare de Cornavin and get off at the Vermont stop.
Bus 8: Depart from Gare de Cornavin and get off at the UIT stop.
Tram 15: departs from Cornavin station and alights at Sismondi stop.
Whether you come by public transport or taxi, it will take you around 15 minutes to reach the CICG from Geneva International Airport.
Bus 5: Depart from the airport and get off at the Vermont stop.
By taxi: Approximately 15 minutes (depending on traffic).
